96  // UNITS IN INPUT FILES
97  // ... Always use atomic units
98  // ... ... Positions in a0 (bohr)
99  // ... ... Multipole moment of rank k in e(a0)**k
100  // ... ... Dipole polarizability in A³ (Angstrom cubed)
101 
102  // UNITS USED INTERNALLY
103  // ... Use nm instead of a0 and A
104  // ... ... Positions in nm
105  // ... ... Multipole moment of rank k in e(nm)**k
106  // ... ... Dipole polarizability in nm³
107 
108  // CONVERSION FACTORS
109  // ... Electric field (N/C) = Electric field (int)
110  // * 1/4PiEps0(SI) * e * 1e+18
111  // ... Energy (eV) = Energy (int) * 1/4PiEps0(SI) * e * 1e+09
112  //
113  // ... Potential (V) = Potential(int) * 1/4PiEps0(SI) * e * 1e+0.9
114

289  inline double T22s_20() { return R5 * 0.5 * sqrt(3) * (35*rbz*rbz*rax*ray - 5*rax*ray + 10*rbz*rax*cyz + 10*rbz*ray*cxz + 2*cxz*cyz); }
290  inline double T21s_21c() { return R5 * (35*rbx*rbz*ray*raz + 5*rbx*ray*czz + 5*rbx*raz*cyz + 5*rbz*ray*czx + 5*rbz*raz*cyx + cyx*czz + czx*cyz); }
291  inline double T22c_21c() { return R5 * 0.5 * (35*rbx*rbz*rax*rax - 35*rbx*rbz*ray*ray + 10*rbx*rax*cxz - 10*rbx*ray*cyz + 10*rbz*rax*cxx - 10*rbz*ray*cyx + 2*cxx*cxz - 2*cyx*cyz); }
292  inline double T22s_21c() { return R5 * (35*rbx*rbz*rax*ray + 5*rbx*rax*cyz + 5*rbx*ray*cxz + 5*rbz*rax*cyx + 5*rbz*ray*cxx + cxx*cyz + cyx*cxz); }
293  inline double T22c_21s() { return R5 * 0.5 * (35*rby*rbz*rax*rax - 35*rby*rbz*ray*ray + 10*rby*rax*cxz - 10*rby*ray*cyz + 10*rbz*rax*cxy - 10*rbz*ray*cyy + 2*cxy*cxz - 2*cyy*cyz); }
294  inline double T22s_21s() { return R5 * (35*rby*rbz*rax*ray + 5*rby*rax*cyz + 5*rby*ray*cxz + 5*rbz*rax*cyy + 5*rbz*ray*cxy + cxy*cyz + cyy*cxz); }
295  inline double T22s_22c() { return R5 * 0.5 * (35*rbx*rbx*rax*ray - 35*rby*rby*rax*ray + 10*rbx*rax*cyx + 10*rbx*ray*cxx - 10*rby*rax*cyy - 10*rby*ray*cxy + 2*cxx*cyx - 2*cxy*cyy); }
296 
297  Topology *_top;
298  ZMultipole *_em;
299 
300  };

642 void ZMultipole::EStatify(Topology *top, Property *options) {
643 
644  cout << endl << "... ... Estatify system: ";
645 
646  string key = "options.zmultipole";
647  string allocFile = options->get(key+".multipoles").as<string> ();
648 
649  // ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ //
650  // Load polar-site indices from XML //
651  // ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ //
652 
653  // => Output to maps:
654  map<string, vector<int> > alloc_frag_mpoleIdx;
655  map<string, vector<string> > alloc_frag_mpoleName;
656  map<string, string > alloc_seg_mpoleFiles_n;
657  map<string, string > alloc_seg_mpoleFiles_e;
658  map<string, string > alloc_seg_mpoleFiles_h;
659 
660  Property allocation; // <- Which polar sites are part of which fragment?
661  load_property_from_xml(allocation, allocFile.c_str());
662 
663 
664  /* --- MULTIPOLES.XML Structure ---
665  *
666  * <topology>
667  *
668  * <molecules>
669  * <molecule>
670  * <name></name>
671  *
672  * <segments>
673  *
674  * <segment>
675  * <name>DCV</name>
676  *
677  * <multipoles_n></multipoles_n>
678  * <multipoles_e></multipoles_e>
679  * <multipoles_h></multipoles_h>
680  *
681  * <map2md></map2md>
682  *
683  * <fragments>
684  * <fragment>
685  * <name></name>
686  * <mpoles></mpoles>
687  * </fragment>
688  * </fragments>
689  * ...
690  * ...
691  */
692 
693 
694  key = "topology.molecules.molecule";
695  list<Property *> mols = allocation.Select(key);
696  list<Property *>::iterator molit;
697  for (molit = mols.begin(); molit != mols.end(); molit++) {
698 
699  string molName = (*molit)->get("name").as<string> ();
700 
701  key = "segments.segment";
702  list<Property *> segs = (*molit)->Select(key);
703  list<Property *>::iterator segit;
704 
705  for (segit = segs.begin(); segit != segs.end(); segit++) {
706 
707  string segName = (*segit)->get("name").as<string> ();
708 
709  // GDMA filenames for cation (h), neutral (n), anion (e) state
710  string mpoleFile_n = (*segit)->get("multipoles_n").as<string> ();
711  alloc_seg_mpoleFiles_n[segName] = mpoleFile_n;
712  if ( (*segit)->exists("multipoles_e")) {
713  string mpoleFile_e = (*segit)->get("multipoles_e").as<string>();
714  alloc_seg_mpoleFiles_e[segName] = mpoleFile_e;
715  }
716  if ( (*segit)->exists("multipoles_h")) {
717  string mpoleFile_h = (*segit)->get("multipoles_h").as<string>();
718  alloc_seg_mpoleFiles_h[segName] = mpoleFile_h;
719  }
720 
721  // Default: Project multipoles onto rigidified coordinates
722  if ( (*segit)->exists("map2md")) {
723  int map2md = (*segit)->get("map2md").as<int>();
724  _map2md[segName] = (map2md == 0) ? false : true;
725  }
726  else {
727  _map2md[segName] = false; // i.e. map to rigidified coordinates
728  }
729 
730  key = "fragments.fragment";
731  list<Property *> frags = (*segit)->Select(key);
732  list<Property *>::iterator fragit;
733 
734  for (fragit = frags.begin(); fragit != frags.end(); fragit++) {
735 
736  string fragName = (*fragit)->get("name").as<string> ();
737  string mapKeyName = fragName + segName + molName;
738 
739  string mpoles = (*fragit)->get("mpoles").as<string> ();
740 
741  Tokenizer tokPoles(mpoles, " \t\n");
742  vector<string> mpoleInfo;
743  tokPoles.ToVector(mpoleInfo);
744 
745  vector<int> mpoleIdcs;
746  vector<string> mpoleNames;
747 
748  vector<string> ::iterator strit;
749  for (strit=mpoleInfo.begin(); strit<mpoleInfo.end(); strit++) {
750 
751  Tokenizer tokPoleInfo( (*strit), " :");
752  vector<string> poleInfo;
753  tokPoleInfo.ToVector(poleInfo);
754 
755  int mpoleIdx = boost::lexical_cast<int>(poleInfo[0]);
756  string mpoleName = poleInfo[1];
757 
758  mpoleIdcs.push_back(mpoleIdx);
759  mpoleNames.push_back(mpoleName);
760 
761  }
762 
763  alloc_frag_mpoleIdx[mapKeyName] = mpoleIdcs;
764  alloc_frag_mpoleName[mapKeyName] = mpoleNames;
765  }
766  }
767  }
768 
769  // ++++++++++++++++++++++ //
770  // Parse GDMA punch files //
771  // ++++++++++++++++++++++ //
772 
773  // => Output to APolarSite Container (template container)
774  map<string, vector<APolarSite*> > map_seg_APolarSites;
775  map<string, vector<bool> > map_seg_chrgStates;
776 
777 
778  // Multipoles for neutral state
779  int state = 0;
780  map<string, string > ::iterator strit;
781  for (strit = alloc_seg_mpoleFiles_n.begin();
782  strit != alloc_seg_mpoleFiles_n.end();
783  strit++) {
784 
785  string segName = strit->first;
786  string filename = strit->second;
787 
788  vector< APolarSite* > poles = ParseGdmaFile(filename, state);
789 
790  map_seg_APolarSites[segName] = poles;
791  map_seg_chrgStates[segName].resize(3);
792  map_seg_chrgStates[segName][0] = false; // <- negative
793  map_seg_chrgStates[segName][1] = true; // <- neutral
794  map_seg_chrgStates[segName][2] = false; // <- positive
795  poles.clear();
796 
797  }
798 
799  // Multipoles for negative state
800  state = -1;
801  if ( alloc_seg_mpoleFiles_e.size() ) {
802  for (strit = alloc_seg_mpoleFiles_e.begin();
803  strit != alloc_seg_mpoleFiles_e.end();
804  strit++) {
805  string segName = strit->first;
806  string filename = strit->second;
807 
808  vector< APolarSite* > polesAnion = ParseGdmaFile(filename, state);
809  map_seg_chrgStates[segName][state+1] = true;
810 
811  // Merge with polar sites for neutral state
812  vector< APolarSite* > polesNeutral = map_seg_APolarSites[segName];
813 
814  assert(polesAnion.size() == polesNeutral.size());
815  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < polesNeutral.size(); i++) {
816 
817  polesNeutral[i]->setQs( polesAnion[i]->getQs(state), state );
818  polesNeutral[i]->setPs( polesAnion[i]->getPs(state), state );
819  delete polesAnion[i];
820  }
821  polesAnion.clear();
822  }
823  }
824 
825  // Multipoles for positive state
826  state = +1;
827  if ( alloc_seg_mpoleFiles_h.size() ) {
828  for (strit = alloc_seg_mpoleFiles_h.begin();
829  strit != alloc_seg_mpoleFiles_h.end();
830  strit++) {
831  string segName = strit->first;
832  string filename = strit->second;
833 
834  vector< APolarSite* > polesCation = ParseGdmaFile(filename, state);
835  map_seg_chrgStates[segName][state+1] = true;
836 
837  // Merge with polar sites for neutral state
838  vector< APolarSite* > polesNeutral = map_seg_APolarSites[segName];
839 
840  assert(polesCation.size() == polesNeutral.size());
841  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < polesNeutral.size(); i++) {
842 
843  polesNeutral[i]->setQs( polesCation[i]->getQs(state), state );
844  polesNeutral[i]->setPs( polesCation[i]->getPs(state), state );
845  delete polesCation[i];
846  }
847  polesCation.clear();
848  }
849  }
850 
851  // +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ //
852  // Forward information on polar-site templates to topology //
853  // +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ //
854 
855  // Containers to use for mapping
856  // map<string, vector<APolarSite*> > map_seg_APolarSites;
857  // map<string, vector<int> > alloc_frag_mpoleIdx;
858  // map<string, vector<string> > alloc_frag_mpoleName;
859 
860  // TO CONTINUE FROM HERE ...
861  // Loop over segments, loop over fragments in segments.
862  // => For each segment, look up associated polar sites using map 1;
863  // => For each fragment, look up associated
864  // polar sites idcs. using map 2;
865  // => For each index in retrieved container, create new polar site,
866  // importing information from polar site container of segment
867  // => Translate positions to MD frame, copy local frame from
868  // fragment
869 
870  _map_seg_APolarSites = map_seg_APolarSites;
871  _map_seg_chrgStates = map_seg_chrgStates;
872  _alloc_frag_mpoleIdx = alloc_frag_mpoleIdx;
873  _alloc_frag_mpoleName = alloc_frag_mpoleName;
874 
875 }

896 vector<vec> ZMultipole::ParseCubeFileHeader(string filename) {
897 
898  vector< vec > cube;
899  cube.resize(5);
900 
901  // STRUCTURE CUBE CONTAINER
902  // 0 1 2 3 4
903  // | | | | | |
904  // ox oy oz Nx Ny Nz xx xy xz yx yy yz zx zy zz
905 
906  std::string line;
907  int lineCount = 0;
908 
909  double Nx = 0;
910  double Ny = 0;
911  double Nz = 0;
912  double BOHR2NM = 0.0529189379;
913  double ANGSTROM2NM = 0.1;
914  double ext2nm = BOHR2NM;
915 
916  std::ifstream intt;
917  intt.open(filename.c_str());
918 
919  if (intt.is_open()) {
920  while (intt.good()) {
921 
922  ++lineCount;
923 
924  std::getline(intt, line);
925  vector<string> split;
926  Tokenizer toker(line, " ");
927  toker.ToVector(split);
928 
929  // First two lines are comment lines
930  if (lineCount == 1 || lineCount == 2) { continue; }
931 
932 
933 
934  // Skip empty lines
935  if ( split.size() == 0) { continue; }
936 
937  // => Interesting information here
938  if (lineCount == 3) {
939 
940  assert( split.size() == 4 );
941  double ox = boost::lexical_cast<double>( split[1] );
942  double oy = boost::lexical_cast<double>( split[2] );
943  double oz = boost::lexical_cast<double>( split[3] );
944 
945  cube[0] = vec(ox, oy, oz);
946  }
947 
948  /*
949  STRUCTURE SAMPLE CPMD CUBE FILE
950  OUTER LOOP: X, MIDDLE LOOP: Y, INNER LOOP: Z
951  3 0.000000 0.000000 0.000000
952  40 0.283459 0.000000 0.000000
953  40 0.000000 0.283459 0.000000
954  40 0.000000 0.000000 0.283459
955  8 0.000000 5.570575 5.669178 5.593517
956  1 0.000000 5.562867 5.669178 7.428055
957  1 0.000000 7.340606 5.669178 5.111259
958  : : : : : :
959  : : : : : :
960  : : : : : :
961  In this case there will be 40 x 40 x 40 floating point values
962  : : : : : :
963  : : : : : :
964  : : : : : :
965  */
966 
967  if (lineCount == 4) {
968 
969  assert( split.size() == 4 );
970  Nx = boost::lexical_cast<double>( split[0] );
971  ext2nm = (Nx > 0) ? BOHR2NM : ANGSTROM2NM;
972  Nx = (Nx >= 0) ? Nx : -Nx;
973  double xx = ext2nm * boost::lexical_cast<double>( split[1] );
974  double xy = ext2nm * boost::lexical_cast<double>( split[2] );
975  double xz = ext2nm * boost::lexical_cast<double>( split[3] );
976 
977  cube[2] = vec(xx, xy, xz);
978  }
979 
980  if (lineCount == 5) {
981 
982  assert( split.size() == 4 );
983  Ny = boost::lexical_cast<double>( split[0] );
984  ext2nm = (Ny > 0) ? BOHR2NM : ANGSTROM2NM;
985  Ny = (Ny >= 0) ? Ny : -Ny;
986  double yx = ext2nm * boost::lexical_cast<double>( split[1] );
987  double yy = ext2nm * boost::lexical_cast<double>( split[2] );
988  double yz = ext2nm * boost::lexical_cast<double>( split[3] );
989 
990  cube[3] = vec(yx, yy, yz);
991  }
992 
993  if (lineCount == 6) {
994 
995  assert( split.size() == 4 );
996  Nz = boost::lexical_cast<double>( split[0] );
997  ext2nm = (Nz > 0) ? BOHR2NM : ANGSTROM2NM;
998  Nz = (Nz >= 0) ? Nz : -Nz;
999  double zx = ext2nm * boost::lexical_cast<double>( split[1] );
1000  double zy = ext2nm * boost::lexical_cast<double>( split[2] );
1001  double zz = ext2nm * boost::lexical_cast<double>( split[3] );
1002 
1003  cube[4] = vec(zx, zy, zz);
1004  cube[1] = vec(Nx, Ny, Nz);
1005  }
1006 
1007  // Header at finish?
1008  if (lineCount > 6) {
1009  break;
1010  }
1011  }
1012  }
1013  else { cout << endl << "ERROR: No such file " << filename << endl; }
1014 
1015  // Convert origin
1016  cube[0] *= ext2nm;
1017 
1018  return cube;
1019 }

1165 void ZMultipole::CalculateESP(vector< APolarSite* > &poles, FILE *out) {
1166

1168  Interactor actor = Interactor(NULL, this);
1169  vector< APolarSite* >::iterator pit;
1170

1172

1181

1227  for (int j = 0; j < Ny; ++j) {
1228  for ( int k = 0; k < Nz; ++k) {

1243  }

1245  }
1246  }

1256  E += actor.EnergyInterESP(*(*pit), *(*pit2));

1485 void ZMultipole::CalculateAlphaRigid(vector< APolarSite* > &poles,
1486  FILE *out, bool system) {
1487 
1488  vector< APolarSite* > ::iterator pit;
1489 
1490  double axx, axy, axz; // |
1491  double ayx, ayy, ayz; // |-> Polarizability tensor
1492  double azx, azy, azz; // |
1493 
1494  double siteU1x, siteU1y, siteU1z; // |-> Molecular ind. dipole
1495 
1496  double extFx, extFy, extFz; // |-> External applied field
1497 
1498  // +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ //
1499  // External field in x-direction //
1500  // +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ //
1501 
1502  siteU1x = siteU1y = siteU1z = 0.0;
1503 
1504  extFx = 0.1;
1505  extFy = 0.0;
1506  extFz = 0.0;
1507 
1508  // Set permanent field
1509  for (pit = poles.begin(); pit < poles.end(); ++pit) {
1510  (*pit)->FPx = extFx;
1511  (*pit)->FPy = extFy;
1512  (*pit)->FPz = extFz;
1513  }
1514 
1515  // Calculate induction field
1516  this->SiteAlphaInduce(NULL, poles);
1517 
1518  // Add up ind. dpl.s to yield molecular U1
1519  for (pit = poles.begin(); pit < poles.end(); ++pit) {
1520  siteU1x += (*pit)->U1x;
1521  siteU1y += (*pit)->U1y;
1522  siteU1z += (*pit)->U1z;
1523  }
1524 
1525  // Calculate associated column of polarizability tensor
1526  axx = - siteU1x / extFx;
1527  ayx = - siteU1y / extFx;
1528  azx = - siteU1z / extFx;
1529 
1530  // +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ //
1531  // External field in y-direction //
1532  // +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ //
1533 
1534  siteU1x = siteU1y = siteU1z = 0.0;
1535 
1536  extFx = 0.0;
1537  extFy = 0.1;
1538  extFz = 0.0;
1539 
1540  // Set permanent field
1541  for (pit = poles.begin(); pit < poles.end(); ++pit) {
1542  (*pit)->FPx = extFx;
1543  (*pit)->FPy = extFy;
1544  (*pit)->FPz = extFz;
1545  }
1546 
1547  // Calculate induction field
1548  this->SiteAlphaInduce(NULL, poles);
1549 
1550  // Add up ind. dpl.s to yield molecular U1
1551  for (pit = poles.begin(); pit < poles.end(); ++pit) {
1552  siteU1x += (*pit)->U1x;
1553  siteU1y += (*pit)->U1y;
1554  siteU1z += (*pit)->U1z;
1555  }
1556 
1557  // Calculate associated column of polarizability tensor
1558  axy = - siteU1x / extFy;
1559  ayy = - siteU1y / extFy;
1560  azy = - siteU1z / extFy;
1561 
1562  // +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ //
1563  // External field in z-direction //
1564  // +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ //
1565 
1566  siteU1x = siteU1y = siteU1z = 0.0;
1567 
1568  extFx = 0.0;
1569  extFy = 0.0;
1570  extFz = 0.1;
1571 
1572  // Set permanent field
1573  for (pit = poles.begin(); pit < poles.end(); ++pit) {
1574  (*pit)->FPx = extFx;
1575  (*pit)->FPy = extFy;
1576  (*pit)->FPz = extFz;
1577  }
1578 
1579  // Calculate induction field
1580  this->SiteAlphaInduce(NULL, poles);
1581 
1582  // Add up ind. dpl.s to yield molecular U1
1583  for (pit = poles.begin(); pit < poles.end(); ++pit) {
1584  siteU1x += (*pit)->U1x;
1585  siteU1y += (*pit)->U1y;
1586  siteU1z += (*pit)->U1z;
1587  }
1588 
1589  // Calculate associated column of polarizability tensor
1590  axz = - siteU1x / extFz;
1591  ayz = - siteU1y / extFz;
1592  azz = - siteU1z / extFz;
1593 
1594  // +++++++++++++++++++++++++++ //
1595  // Sum, Trace, Diagonalization //
1596  // +++++++++++++++++++++++++++ //
1597 
1598  // Sum over atomic polarizabilities
1599  double SUM_alpha = 0.0;
1600  for (pit = poles.begin(); pit < poles.end(); ++pit) {
1601  SUM_alpha += (*pit)->getIsoP();
1602  }
1603 
1604  double NM3_2_A3 = 1000.;
1605  SUM_alpha *= NM3_2_A3;
1606 
1607  // TODO Diagonalize polarizability tensor
1608  // For now, trace is enough
1609  double ISO_alpha = (axx + ayy + azz) / 3.;
1610 
1611  ISO_alpha *= NM3_2_A3;
1612 
1613  // Eigenvalues of polarizability tensor
1614  matrix alpha = matrix( vec(axx,ayx,azx),
1615  vec(axy,ayy,azy),
1616  vec(axz,ayz,azz) );
1617  matrix::eigensystem_t EIGEN;
1618  alpha.SolveEigensystem(EIGEN);
1619 
1620 
1621  if (! system) {
1622  cout << endl << "... ... ... ... Sum over atomic alphas: "
1623  << SUM_alpha << " A**3.";
1624  cout << endl << "... ... ... ... 1/3 trace of alpha tensor: "
1625  << ISO_alpha << " A**3.";
1626  cout << endl << "... ... ... ... Eigenvalues: "
1627  << EIGEN.eigenvalues[0]*NM3_2_A3 << " A**3, "
1628  << EIGEN.eigenvalues[1]*NM3_2_A3 << " A**3, "
1629  << EIGEN.eigenvalues[2]*NM3_2_A3 << " A**3. ";
1630  }
1631 
1632  if (_alphaOutFile != "noname" && _alphaOutFile != "") {
1633 
1634  vec x = EIGEN.eigenvecs[0];
1635  vec y = EIGEN.eigenvecs[1];
1636  vec z = EIGEN.eigenvecs[2];
1637 
1638  if (! system) {
1639  fprintf(out, "Polarizability tensor in global frame \n");
1640  fprintf(out, "%4.7f %4.7f %4.7f \n", axx*NM3_2_A3, axy*NM3_2_A3, axz*NM3_2_A3);
1641  fprintf(out, "%4.7f %4.7f %4.7f \n", ayx*NM3_2_A3, ayy*NM3_2_A3, ayz*NM3_2_A3);
1642  fprintf(out, "%4.7f %4.7f %4.7f \n", azx*NM3_2_A3, azy*NM3_2_A3, azz*NM3_2_A3);
1643  fprintf(out, "\n");
1644  fprintf(out, "Polarizability tensor in eigenframe \n");
1645  fprintf(out, "%4.7f %4.7f %4.7f \n", EIGEN.eigenvalues[0]*NM3_2_A3,0.,0.);
1646  fprintf(out, "%4.7f %4.7f %4.7f \n", 0.,EIGEN.eigenvalues[1]*NM3_2_A3,0.);
1647  fprintf(out, "%4.7f %4.7f %4.7f \n", 0.,0.,EIGEN.eigenvalues[2]*NM3_2_A3);
1648  fprintf(out, "\n");
1649  fprintf(out, "Polarizability tensor main axes \n");
1650  fprintf(out, "%4.7f %4.7f %4.7f \n", x.getX(),x.getY(),x.getZ());
1651  fprintf(out, "%4.7f %4.7f %4.7f \n", y.getX(),y.getY(),y.getZ());
1652  fprintf(out, "%4.7f %4.7f %4.7f \n", z.getX(),z.getY(),z.getZ());
1653  }
1654  else {
1655  fprintf(out, "%4.7f %4.7f %4.7f %4.7f %4.7f ",
1656  ISO_alpha, SUM_alpha,
1657  EIGEN.eigenvalues[0]*NM3_2_A3,
1658  EIGEN.eigenvalues[1]*NM3_2_A3,
1659  EIGEN.eigenvalues[2]*NM3_2_A3);
1660  }
1661  }

1669 void ZMultipole::SiteAlphaInduce(Topology *top, vector<APolarSite*> &poles) {
1670 
1671  int maxIter = this->_maxIter;
1672  double wSOR = this->_wSOR_N;
1673  double eTOL = this->_epsTol;
1674 
1675  vector< APolarSite* >::iterator pit1;
1676  vector< APolarSite* >::iterator pit2;
1677 
1678  Interactor actor = Interactor(top, this);
1679 
1680  // Induce to first order
1681  for (pit1 = poles.begin(); pit1 < poles.end(); ++pit1) {
1682  (*pit1)->InduceDirect();
1683  }
1684 
1685 
1686  int iter = 0;
1687  for ( ; iter < maxIter; ++iter) {
1688 
1689  // Reset induction field
1690  for (pit1 = poles.begin(); pit1 < poles.end(); ++pit1) {
1691  (*pit1)->ResetFieldU();
1692  }
1693 
1694  // Calculate higher-order induction field
1695  for (pit1 = poles.begin(); pit1 < poles.end(); ++pit1) {
1696  for (pit2 = pit1 + 1; pit2 < poles.end(); ++pit2) {
1697  actor.FieldInduAlpha(*(*pit1),*(*pit2));
1698  }
1699  }
1700 
1701  // Induce dipoles
1702  for (pit1 = poles.begin(); pit1 < poles.end(); ++pit1) {
1703  (*pit1)->Induce(wSOR);
1704  }
1705 
1706  // Check for convergence
1707  bool converged = true;
1708  double maxdU = -1;
1709  double avgdU = 0.0;
1710  int baseN = 0;
1711 
1712  for (pit1 = poles.begin(); pit1 < poles.end(); ++pit1) {
1713  double dU = (*pit1)->HistdU();
1714  avgdU += dU;
1715  ++baseN;
1716  if ( dU > maxdU ) { maxdU = dU; }
1717  if ( dU > eTOL ) { converged = false; }
1718  }
1719 
1720  avgdU /= baseN;
1721  if (avgdU < eTOL/10.) { converged = true; }
1722 
1723  //cout << endl << "ITER" << iter << " | MAX dU " << maxdU
1724  // << " | AVG dU " << avgdU;
1725 
1726  // Break if converged
1727  if (converged) { break; }
1728  else if (iter == maxIter - 1) {
1729  cout << endl << "... ... ... "
1730  << "WARNING Induced multipoles did not converge to precision: "
1731  << " AVG dU:U " << avgdU << flush;
1732  break;
1733  }
1734  }
1735 }

2464  int maxI = this->_master->_maxIter;
2465

2468  vector< APolarSite* > ::iterator pit1;
2469  vector< APolarSite* > ::iterator pit2;
2470 
2471  // ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ //
2472  // Inter-site fields (arising from perm. m'poles) //
2473  // ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ //
2474 
2475  for (sit1 = _polsPolSphere.begin();
2476  sit1 < _polsPolSphere.end();
2477  ++sit1) {
2478  for (sit2 = sit1 + 1;
2479  sit2 < _polsPolSphere.end();
2480  ++sit2) {
2481 
2482  for (pit1 = (*sit1).begin(); pit1 < (*sit1).end(); ++pit1) {
2483  for (pit2 = (*sit2).begin(); pit2 < (*sit2).end(); ++pit2) {
2484 
2485  _actor.FieldPerm(*(*pit1), *(*pit2));
2486  }}
2487  }}
2488 
2489  // Permanent fields generated by outer shell
2490  // (Outer shell itself is treated as non-polarizable)
2491  for (sit1 = _polsPolSphere.begin();
2492  sit1 < _polsPolSphere.end();
2493  ++sit1) {
2494  for (sit2 = _polsOutSphere.begin();
2495  sit2 < _polsOutSphere.end();
2496  ++sit2) {
2497 
2498  for (pit1 = (*sit1).begin(); pit1 < (*sit1).end(); ++pit1) {
2499  for (pit2 = (*sit2).begin(); pit2 < (*sit2).end(); ++pit2) {
2500 
2501  _actor.FieldPerm(*(*pit1), *(*pit2));
2502  }}
2503  }}
2504 
2505  // +++++++++++++++++++ //
2506  // 1st-order induction //
2507  // +++++++++++++++++++ //
2508 
2509  if (state == 0) { // OVERRIDE
2510  for (sit1 = _polsPolSphere.begin();
2511  sit1 < _polsPolSphere.end();
2512  ++sit1) {
2513 
2514  for (pit1 = (*sit1).begin(); pit1 < (*sit1).end(); ++pit1) {
2515  (*pit1)->InduceDirect();
2516  }
2517  }
2518  }
2519 
2520 
2521 
2522  // ++++++++++++++++++++++ //
2523  // Higher-order induction //
2524  // ++++++++++++++++++++++ //
2525 
2526  int iter = 0;
2527  for ( ; iter < maxI; ++iter) {
2528 
2529  for (sit1 = _polsPolSphere.begin();
2530  sit1 < _polsPolSphere.end();
2531  ++sit1) {
2532 
2533  for (pit1 = (*sit1).begin(); pit1 < (*sit1).end(); ++pit1) {
2534  (*pit1)->ResetFieldU();
2535  }
2536  }
2537 
2538  for (sit1 = _polsPolSphere.begin();
2539  sit1 < _polsPolSphere.end();
2540  ++sit1) {
2541 
2542  for (pit1 = (*sit1).begin(); pit1 < (*sit1).end(); ++pit1) {
2543  for (pit2 = pit1 + 1; pit2 < (*sit1).end(); ++pit2) {
2544 
2545  _actor.FieldIndu(*(*pit1),*(*pit2));
2546  }}
2547  }
2548 
2549  for (sit1 = _polsPolSphere.begin();
2550  sit1 < _polsPolSphere.end();
2551  ++sit1) {
2552  for (sit2 = sit1 + 1;
2553  sit2 < _polsPolSphere.end();
2554  ++sit2) {
2555 
2556  for (pit1 = (*sit1).begin(); pit1 < (*sit1).end(); ++pit1) {
2557  for (pit2 = (*sit2).begin(); pit2 < (*sit2).end(); ++pit2) {
2558 
2559  _actor.FieldIndu(*(*pit1), *(*pit2));
2560  }}
2561  }}
2562 
2563  for (sit1 = _polsPolSphere.begin();
2564  sit1 < _polsPolSphere.end();
2565  ++sit1) {
2566 
2567  for (pit1 = (*sit1).begin(); pit1 < (*sit1).end(); ++pit1) {
2568  (*pit1)->Induce(wSOR);
2569  }
2570  }
2571 
2572  bool converged = true;
2573  double maxdU = -1;
2574  double avgdU = 0.0;
2575  int baseN = 0;
2576  for (sit1 = _polsPolSphere.begin();
2577  sit1 < _polsPolSphere.end();
2578  ++sit1) {
2579 
2580  for (pit1 = (*sit1).begin(); pit1 < (*sit1).end(); ++pit1) {
2581  double dU = (*pit1)->HistdU();
2582  avgdU += dU;
2583  ++baseN;
2584  if ( dU > maxdU ) { maxdU = dU; }
2585  if ( dU > eTOL ) { converged = false; }
2586  }
2587  }
2588  avgdU /= baseN;
2589  if (avgdU < eTOL/10.) { converged = true; }
2590 
2591 
2592  // Break if converged
2593  if (converged) {
2594  break;
2595  }
2596  else if (iter == maxI - 1) {
2597  this->_master->LockCout();

2599  << _seg->getId() << " - state " << state
2600  << " did not converge to precision: "
2601  << " AVG dU:U " << avgdU << flush;
2602  this->_master->UnlockCout();
2603  break;
2604  }
2605  }
2606 
2607  return iter;
2608 }

2775 inline double ZMultipole::Interactor::PotentialPerm(vec r,
2776  APolarSite &pol) {
2777 
2778  // NOTE >>> e12 points from polar site 1 to polar site 2 <<< NOTE //
2779  e12 = pol.getPos() - r;
2780  R = 1/abs(e12);
2781  R2 = R*R;
2782  R3 = R2*R;
2783  R4 = R3*R;
2784  R5 = R4*R;
2785  e12 *= R;
2786 
2787 
2788 
2789 
2790  rbx = - pol._locX * e12;
2791  rby = - pol._locY * e12;
2792  rbz = - pol._locZ * e12;
2793 
2794  double phi00 = 0.0;
2795 
2796  phi00 += T00_00() * pol.Q00;
2797 
2798  if (pol._rank > 0) {
2799  phi00 += T00_1x() * pol.Q1x;
2800  phi00 += T00_1y() * pol.Q1y;
2801  phi00 += T00_1z() * pol.Q1z;
2802  }
2803 
2804  if (pol._rank > 1) {
2805  phi00 += T00_20() * pol.Q20;
2806  phi00 += T00_21c() * pol.Q21c;
2807  phi00 += T00_21s() * pol.Q21s;
2808  phi00 += T00_22c() * pol.Q22c;
2809  phi00 += T00_22s() * pol.Q22s;
2810  }
2811 
2812  return phi00;
2813 }
2814 
2818 inline vec ZMultipole::Interactor::FieldPermESF(vec r,
2819  APolarSite &pol) {
2820  // NOTE >>> e12 points from polar site 1 to polar site 2 <<< NOTE //
2821  e12 = pol.getPos() - r;
2822  R = 1/abs(e12);
2823  R2 = R*R;
2824  R3 = R2*R;
2825  R4 = R3*R;
2826  R5 = R4*R;
2827  e12 *= R;
2828 
2829  rax = e12.getX();
2830  ray = e12.getY();
2831  raz = e12.getZ();
2832  rbx = - rax;
2833  rby = - ray;
2834  rbz = - raz;
2835 
2836  cxx = 1;
2837  cxy = 0;
2838  cxz = 0;
2839  cyx = 0;
2840  cyy = 1;
2841  cyz = 0;
2842  czx = 0;
2843  czy = 0;
2844  czz = 1;
2845 
2846  double Fx = 0.0;
2847  double Fy = 0.0;
2848  double Fz = 0.0;
2849 
2850  // Field generated by rank-0 m'pole
2851  Fx += T1x_00() * pol.Q00;
2852  Fy += T1y_00() * pol.Q00;
2853  Fz += T1z_00() * pol.Q00;
2854 
2855  // Field generated by rank-1 m'pole
2856  if (pol._rank > 0) {
2857  Fx += T1x_1x() * pol.Q1x;
2858  Fx += T1x_1y() * pol.Q1y;
2859  Fx += T1x_1z() * pol.Q1z;
2860 
2861  Fy += T1y_1x() * pol.Q1x;
2862  Fy += T1y_1y() * pol.Q1y;
2863  Fy += T1y_1z() * pol.Q1z;
2864 
2865  Fz += T1z_1x() * pol.Q1x;
2866  Fz += T1z_1y() * pol.Q1y;
2867  Fz += T1z_1z() * pol.Q1z;
2868  }
2869 
2870  // Field generated by rank-2 m'pole
2871  if (pol._rank > 1) {
2872  Fx += T1x_20() * pol.Q20;
2873  Fx += T1x_21c() * pol.Q21c;
2874  Fx += T1x_21s() * pol.Q21s;
2875  Fx += T1x_22c() * pol.Q22c;
2876  Fx += T1x_22s() * pol.Q22s;
2877 
2878  Fy += T1y_20() * pol.Q20;
